</div>
Yet it has to happen, especially in transplant cases due to a limited supply of organs.  Do you give the liver to the the person with liver failure due to no fault of their own, or to the alcoholic who has willingly ruined their own liver?  To the young, relatively healthy person or to the older person with a long list of health concerns?  Do we simply give it to whoever was on the list first?  Doesn't it make more sense to give the liver to the person most likely to get the best use out of it rather than someone who is likely to ruin it the same way they ruined their original equipment?
                  
		</div>
