                  Torcer,<br />
well that only proves what I said earlier: around 1/3rd of doctors are complete useless ass bag bastards ! :P<br />
<br />
The SOB endocrinologist who saw me first couldn't give a rats, looked at me and I could hear/see his attitude: &quot;<i>Your fat, so your lazy therefore get to f' away!&quot;...</i>and ignored the evidence in front of his face, incontrivertible hard scientific DATA form multiple blood tests, but he ignored it, because he is a *bigot*. If I wasn't a nice guy, I'd be very unplesant to him. My constitution is shot to hell, but fair bit of my strength has come back thanks to the testosterone shots *grim smile*<br />
<br />
Course I'm fat and &quot;Lazy&quot; nowadays, I've got an extremely debilitating illness, ya bastard! I never CHOSE this. Used to do weight training 3 days out of 4.<br />
Thought it was funny, years ago when I was healthy, doc saying I was over weight, course I was &quot;over weight&quot;, I was built like a brick sh*thouse, muppet! get your head out of Body weight/height charts and *LOOK*, use common sense, FFS. I bench pressed my <i>friends</i>, for fun, back then. *rants at docs* <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
One doc told me &quot;<i>Oh you need to do exercise</i>!&quot; a few years back,since allI can do is walk, andthatlimited to 600-800 yards on a good day *once in a day*, and usually to half that.<br />
 ...in England, they went with the &quot;psychological causitive school&quot; of thought for the cause of ME/CFS...so, they MADE folk do exercise: 1 died, two survived heart attacks (that we know of) cause amazingly this biological illness messes yer heart up, amongst other things (like Lyme Disease and mercury both do).<br />
If I do exercise, I collpase and faint, that's how I first discovered I had this crap:walking to town like I usually did, got sicker and collapsed. &quot;Orthostatic hypotension&quot; is one of the things it does iirc.<br />
<br />
<br />
Back to OP<br />
Mixing that in with the alcoholics is a cheap shot. Yes, alcoholics should be denied it unless they have proof they have been off booze for many years, that's common sense and a specific type of exception. Those folk are *addicts*. If they have beaten their addiciton, fine thewy deserve the livers. If not...sorry, but there's no point wasting all that effort when others need the same thing.<br />
<br />
That *is* different, they are addicts with an addiction which means a transplant will be destroyed very soon. Horrible, but...meh.<br />
<br />
What no one wants ot talk about is the explosion of chronic ill health that's occured. It can't tbe down to simply food/life style, as folk across the globe see similar problems: autism, diabetese etc sky rocketing.<br />
They did a health study up here in Glasgow, trying to find out why so many folk claimed Incapacity Benefit, believing most were scamming...alas for the smart asses...no, there really is excess ill health and it's more than just deprivation, obesity or scamming.<br />
<br />
Whether caused by genetics of folk who suffered too much deprivation for the last 150 years (a real threat as has been discovered), or enviromental poisoning of areas soaked in heavy metals and other crap, or too many household chemicals having an effect we didn't expect, or perhaps some new threat we don't understand yet, possibly synergistic damage on many fronts screwing us up, no one knows.<br />
But they found there is excessive health problems that they couldn't explain. So what's going on?<br />
And dont' blame it on us eating fried Mars bars, lol. Only ever knew one idiot who did that on a dare. <br />
<br />
<br />
Besides which, <b><font color="Red">unhealthy folk keep doctors in a job</font></b>, so those lazy bastards should STFU up and pray THEY never get M.E., multiple sclerosis, hepatitis, or any other such crap.
                  
