                  What if they both wound up on the list at the exact same time?  At some point, someone has to make this sort of decision.  It's unavoidable.<br />
<br />
And even if there was one who was clearly on the list before the other?  What if one's health was deteriorating faster than the other?  If the teenager was deteriorating faster it would probably make sense to bump them up on the list.  If the senior was deteriorating faster, it might not make as much sense to bump them.
                  
