That's a scary proposition then, since morality can be subjective to a point.  A 60 year old man with a family of six to support, and possibly only 20 years to live, versus a 16 year old boy with no similar responsibilities, but a good seventy years of life ahead...even if the decision is made by a panel, and not bound to one person to decide, without setting up some parameters before the decision is necessary just doesn't seem just or fair to me.<br />
<br />
Wish I knew someone who worked in this field who could answer on how it is currently handled, and if its a universal practice, or one that varies from hospital to hospital.
                  
